Java Custom Exception:- Java Provides Features that We Can Create Our Own Exception That is 
Known as Java Custom Excetion For Creating Our Own Exception We Have to Inherite the That Class 
from Exception Class that is Known as User Defined or Custom Exception 

We can Create our Own Exception as Per User Requirement 

Java exceptions cover almost all the general type of exceptions that may occur in the programming
But Sometime we Need to create Our own Custom Exception 

Following are few of the reasons to use custom exceptions:

To catch and provide specific treatment to a subset of existing Java exceptions.

Business logic exceptions: These are the exceptions related to business logic and 
workflow. It is useful for the application users or the developers to understand the exact problem.

Example of Custome Exception

public class WrongFileNameException extends Exception {  
    public WrongFileNameException(String errorMessage) {  
    super(errorMessage);  
    }  
}  
